# Memory Bank
At the start of EVERY task, read all files in memory-bank/ before doing anything.
After significant work, update the relevant memory-bank/ files.
Use /newtask when context gets large to preserve state cleanly.

# Project Rules
- This is a sensitive psychological/clinical domain — be conservative with data handling
- Never hardcode patient data or PII anywhere
- Prefer sklearn pipelines over ad-hoc preprocessing chains
- Keep notebooks and scripts separate: notebooks for exploration, scripts for production logic
- When adding a new model or feature, update memory-bank/systemPatterns.md